data.description: Location! Location! Location! A RARE find! Do Not miss this wonderful opportunity to live in one of Trenton's most beautiful historic, well-maintained cul-de-sac neighborhoods, centrally located and close to downtown. It's a short distance to Thomas Edison State University (.06 miles), Mercer County Community College James Kerney Campus (1.2 miles), NJ State Museum (1.1 miles), Downtown Trenton Public Library, local downtown shops, and restaurants. Enjoy nearby Trenton Thunder baseball games at Trenton Thunder Ballpark and concerts at the downtown War Memorial Coliseum! Additionally, you will be centrally located close to Route 1, I 295, and Route 206. Located only 2.1 miles from Trenton Train station, a 55-minute train ride to Center City Philadelphia, an average of a 1.5-hour train ride to New York City, 15 minutes from shopping malls, and less than 28 minutes from Jackson Premium Outlet and Six Flags!This lovely 3-story brick historic home resides in the heart of West Trenton's historic district on a beautiful tree-lined street. You will have plenty of room in your spacious 6-bedroom, 4-bathroom beautiful brick home full of character from dual French doors, original inlaid hardwood flooring, beautiful molding throughout, lovely wood staircase, built-in cabinets, claw foot tub, and more!The main floor, the heart of the home, has a large spacious living room with archways, a large brick wood-burning fireplace with double French doors on each side of the fireplace, and a separate adjacent spacious dining room with a corner built-in corner cabinet, and a swing door to the kitchen for privacy. The kitchen has black galaxy granite countertops. The year-round sunroom/den/office, with wall-to-wall windows, has a separate side door entrance that leads to your private driveway with a detached 2-car garage. Enjoy your finished basement with recessed lighting, a custom built-in bar, a gas fireplace, a full bath, and a separate office/workout room. The main floor also has a back door entrance to a combined mud/laundry room that leads to your private fenced-in backyard.There are 3 bedrooms located on the second floor which include a very large master bedroom with a full bath, a second bedroom, with a private bath, and a third bedroom overlooking the backyard. There are 3 additional bedrooms on the 3rd floor with 1 full bath and an antique porcelain claw foot tub. The third floor also has a custom deep cedar-lined closet, a hidden jewel.This home features an enclosed backyard with a custom brick-paved patio with lighting. The backyard has a pond surrounded by beautiful maple trees and a great shed for extra storage. Lastly, a brand-new furnace was installed in 2022.Don't miss out! This home has a clear certificate of occupancy and is move-in ready.
